        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-10-29T06:06:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-10-29T06:06:00-05:00" n="200"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <head>200. Telegram 177998 from the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Ivory Coast</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d200fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, <gloss
                            target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 30 Nigeria. Confidential; priority; Limdis.
                        Repeated priority to Lagos. Drafted by Kontos (<gloss target="#t_AF1"
                            >AF</gloss>/AFR–N), cleared in (<gloss target="#t_AF1">AF</gloss>/W),
                        and approved by <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">Newsom</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d200fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">Newsom</persName> expressed his concern that
                            <persName corresp="#p_OLCCO1">Ojukwu</persName> might seek asylum in the
                        United States, which could do much harm to relations with Nigeria.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1970-10-29T06:06:00-05:00">October 29, 1970, 0606Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <pb facs="d200-01" n="1" xml:id="d200-01"/>
                <p>FROM <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">NEWSOM</persName> FOR ROOT</p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>REF</head>
                    <item>(A) STATE 166104 (B) BERN 4101</item>
                </list>
                <p>Swiss refusal asylum to Ojukwu sharply increases our concern that U.S. haven may
                    now be sought. We wish avoid, if at all possible, submission of application for
                    visa to us. The partisan pushing and hauling that may emerge from such a move by
                    Ojukwu could do much harm to our relations with <gloss target="#t_FMG1"
                        >FMG</gloss> plus damage U.S. interests in Nigeria. Unless you perceive
                    substantial objections, request you approach Houphouet-Boigny and indicate U.S.
                    Government would not look with favor on move to seek asylum for Ojukwu in U.S.
                    and express hope that <gloss target="#t_GOIC1">GOIC</gloss> will discourage any
                    inclination to move in this direction. END</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
